The paper deals with algorithms for computing crossing-free strongly monotone drawings of planar graphs, which involves topics such as computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and possibly also social and information networks (cs.SI) since the concept of monotonicity is relevant in these fields.
